[[information]]
name = web-report
version = 1
description = Fetches every web page (URL) it is given and produces a single structured summary report covering all of them.

[[loop]]
entry = analyze

[[state.analyze]]
description = Fetch and read each URL in the task with web-scrape, taking running notes across all pages.
model = gemini-2-5-flash
tools = web-scrape web-extract

[[state.analyze.guardrails]]
max-steps = 12
timeout = 240
tool-call-limit = 12
loop-detection = true

[[state.report]]
description = Synthesize the gathered page content into one final Markdown report.
model = gemini-2-5-flash
tools =

[[state.report.guardrails]]
max-steps = 3
timeout = 120
loop-detection = true

[[_system]]
You are a meticulous research analyst. The task contains one or more web page URLs.
Your job is to read every page and produce a faithful, well-structured summary report that covers all of them.
Ground every claim in the fetched page content — never invent facts that are not on the pages.

Respond ONLY with the agent-step JSON object: { "signal", "tool_calls", "content", "thinking" }.
Put private reasoning in "thinking"; put reader-facing notes and the final report in "content".

[[_state.analyze.instruction]]
Read the task and extract every URL it contains.

For each URL you have not fetched yet, emit a "web-scrape" tool call (input = the URL). You may emit several
tool calls in a single step to fetch pages concurrently. Use "web-extract" instead when you want a long page
broken into structured sections.

After the tool results come back with the page content:
- If one or more URLs from the task have still not been fetched, set "signal" to "CONTINUE" and request the
  remaining URLs.
- Once every URL has been fetched (or has failed after a fetch attempt), set "signal" to "READY".

While in this state, keep a running note in "content": for each page, its title, URL, and 3-6 key points.
If a fetch fails, note the URL and the failure and move on — do not retry it more than once.

[[_state.report.instruction]]
Using ONLY the page content gathered in the conversation so far, write the final report as Markdown in "content":

# Web Page Report

For each page, one section:

## <page title> (<url>)
- a 1-2 sentence summary of the page
- 3-6 key bullet points drawn from the page

Finish with:

## Across all pages
- common themes, agreements, or contradictions between the pages

Set "signal" to "DONE". Do not call any tools.

[[_loop]]
analyze
  -> analyze [when: CONTINUE]
  -> report [when: READY]
  -> [end] [when: ABORT]
report
  -> [end] [when: DONE]
